-- Government Boosts Economic Growth Forecast to 3.4% for 2010, 1.8% for 2011
-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 2010-10-21T08:39:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/government-boosts-economic-growth-forecast-to-3-4-for-2010-1-8-for-2011.html
The German government raised its
forecast for economic growth to 3.4 percent this year and 1.8
percent in 2011, Economy Minister Rainer Bruederle said in
Berlin today. The government previously forecast expansion of
1.4 percent and 1.6 percent, respectively.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Brian Parkin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net  